:\"**Editing class structure**\\n\\nI see that I need to work on the `RunJarTest` class. I can initialize it as static to avoid the complexity of nested classes. I should add public static fields and a main method for clarity. But, I need to be cautious about potential naming conflicts. Resetting methods to private static will help streamline things. By removing the nested class, I’ll keep it all in one file, which simplifies everything. Let’s go ahead and make those edits!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JFb7CHgCJtqf1wldj8aQbQ5D|fc_05e0292de2a14f950169fa88f67b6c81a1aa0c335b850ccaa4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-common/2.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop/hadoop_common/RunJarTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        RunJarTarget.reset();\n        Path jar = createJarWithMainClassManifest(RunJarTarget.class.getName());", "newText": "        resetTarget();\n        Path jar = createJarWithMainClassManifest(RunJarTest.class.getName());"}, {"oldText": "            assertThat(RunJarTarget.wasInvoked()).isTrue();\n            assertThat(RunJarTarget.arguments()).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");", "newText": "            assertThat(targetWasInvoked()).isTrue();\n            assertThat(targetArguments()).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");"}, {"oldText": "public class RunJarTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;", "newText": "public class RunJarTest {\n    private static volatile boolean targetInvoked;\n    private static volatile List<String> targetArguments = List.of();\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;"}, {"oldText": "    public static final class RunJarTarget {\n        private static volatile boolean invoked;\n        private static volatile List<String> arguments = List.of();\n\n        public static void main(String[] args) {\n            invoked = true;\n            arguments = Arrays.asList(args.clone());\n        }\n\n        private static void reset() {\n            invoked =