to a duplicate class being defined by `URLClassLoader`. This could cause issues when `main.invoke` updates static fields in the duplicate class, making assertions fail.\\n\\nOne solution might be to have `main` write arguments to a temp file or a system property for communication between classes. I also need to address dynamic class loading and potential limitations in the Native Image context. I'll look into using unique property keys for temporary storage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading and dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about simplifying with `System.setProperty(\\\"runjar.test.args\\\", String.join(\\\",\\\", args));` since the static method in a class defined by `URLClassLoader` doesn't really need static fields. If the test is compiled correctly, the class resource should be present, allowing me to create a jar that includes the `RunJarTest.class` bytes.\\n\\nHowever, there’s a concern about dependencies, like JUnit, that may be referenced in methods. If only `main` is executed, the class verifier might require all referenced classes. It’s interesting that loading `RunJarTest` could resolve the constant pool lazily.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering string formatting options**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to handle the property string with a separator if the arguments contain certain characters. For arguments like \\\"alpha\\\" and \\\"beta,\\\" I’m not seeing an issue. Instead of using a complex method like storing as \\\"alpha\\\\0beta,\\\" I could simply assert that it equals \\\"alpha,beta.\\\" It seems better to use `String.join(\\\",\\\", args)` instead of needing an import for `Arrays.toString(args)`. That looks cleaner!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Meh5QgUlyntFKWv4DgNaJJ9A|fc_05e0292de2a14f950169fa890cd4a481a18a3ac8b04c28f0d2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-common/2.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop/hadoop_common/RunJarTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;", "newText": "import java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;"}, {"oldText": "import java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;", "newText": "import java.util.Arrays;"}, {"oldText": "public class RunJarTest {\n    private static volatile boolean targetInvoked;\n    private static volatile List<String> targetArguments = List.of();\n\n    @TempDir", "newText": "public class RunJarTest {\n    private static final String INVOKED_PROPERTY = RunJarTest.class.getName() + \".invoked\";\n    private static final String ARGUMENTS_PROPERTY = RunJarTest.class.getName() + \".arguments\";\n\n    @TempDir"}, {"oldText": "            assertThat(targetWasInvoked()).isTrue();\n            assertThat(targetArguments()).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");", "newText": "            assertThat(System.getProperty(INVOKED_PROPERTY)).isEqualTo(\"true\");\n            assertThat(System.getProperty(ARGUMENTS_PROPERTY)).isEqualTo(\"alpha,beta\");"}, {"oldText": "            JarEntry entry = new JarEntry(\"payload.txt\");\n            jarOutput.putNextEntry(entry);\n            jarOutput.write(\"payload\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            jarOutput.closeEntry();", "newText": "            addClassEntry(jarOutput, RunJarTest.class);\n            JarEntry entry = new JarEntry(\"payload.txt\");\n            jarOutput.putNextEntry(entry);\n            jarOutput.write(\"payload\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            jarOutput.closeEntry();"}, {"oldText": "    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        targetInvoked = true;\n        targetArguments = Arrays.asList(args.clone());\n    }\n\n    private static void resetTarget() {\n        targetInvoked = false;\n        targetArguments = List.of();\n    }\n\n    private static boolean targetWasInvoked() {\n        return targetInvoked;\n    }\n\n    private static List<String> targe